  "id": "volatility_compression_breakout_trader",
  "name": "Volatility_Compression_Breakout_Trader",
  "description": "This algorithm identifies volatility compression by calculating the 20-period Average True Range (ATR) on 5-minute bars. It triggers trades when the ATR falls below its 10-period simple moving average and detects a narrowing of the Bollinger Bands, indicating potential breakout opportunities.",
  "algorithm_type": "CandleStickPattern",
  "prompt": "Develop an expert-level TechnicalPattern intraday trading algorithm in Python that identifies and trades on volatility compression and breakout patterns using the following criteria: compute the 20-period Average True Range (ATR) on 5-minute bars to measure volatility compression when ATR falls below its 10-period simple moving average; simultaneously detect a narrowing Bollinger Bands Width (20, 2 std dev) below its 15-period moving average as a confirmation of price consolidation; enter a long position when price breaks above the upper Bollinger Band on high volume defined as above the 20-period volume moving average, with ATR signaling expansion (current ATR > 10-period SMA ATR); enter a short position on a breakout below the lower Bollinger Band under symmetrical volume and ATR expansion conditions; exit trades when price retraces to the 10-period EMA or when a reversal candlestick pattern (Hammer or Shooting Star) forms at the opposite Bollinger Band; include stop-losses based on 1.5 times ATR from entry price; ensure the algorithm dynamically adjusts to volatility shifts by recalculating ATR and Bollinger Bands in real-time on the 5-minute chart.",
